HEADWORD: Gnathopodite
<hw>Gna*thop"o*dite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool,)</fld>
<def>Any leglike appendage of a crustacean, when modified wholly, or in
part, to serve as a jaw, esp. one of the maxillipeds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gnathostegite</ent>⟦br⟧
